10641 0 obj
<</AP<</N 10643 0 R >>/C[ 1 0 0]/CA 1/Contents(Headers are pieces of metadata sent along with data in communication protocols such as HTTP, email, or files. They provide information about the content, sender, receiver, format, and how the data should be handled.\n\nIn HTTP \(Web Requests\)\n\nWhen your browser requests a web page, it sends headers like:\n\nGET /index.html HTTP/1.1\nHost: example.com\nUser-Agent: Chrome\nAccept: text/html\n\nAnd the server responds with headers such as:\n\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nContent-Type: text/html\nContent-Length: 1024\n\nCommon HTTP headers:\n\nHost Ö Website being requested.\nUser-Agent Ö Information about the client/browser.\nContent-Type Ö Type of data being sent \(e.g., JSON, HTML\).\nAuthorization Ö Credentials or tokens for authentication.\nCookie Ö Session information.\r\n\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n\r\nMany people understand what headers are, but not why we need them in this specific code.\n\nLet's look at your code:\n\nHttpHeaders headers =\n        new HttpHeaders\(\);\n\nheaders.setContentType\(\n        MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON\n\);\nWhat are we sending to Flask?\n\nWe are sending:\n\n{\n   "emailText":\n   "You won a lottery"\n}\n\nSpring knows it's JSON.\n\nBut Flask doesn't know that yet.\n\nImagine you receive a package.\n\nInside is:\n\n{\n   "emailText":\n   "You won a lottery"\n}\n\nBut nobody tells you what format it is.\n\nCould be:\n\nJSON\nXML\nPlain Text\nCSV\n\nHow would you know?\n\nThat's exactly why we use headers.\n\nThe header tells Flask:\n\nContent-Type:\napplication/json\n\nMeaning:\n\n"The body I'm sending is JSON."\n\nWithout Header\n\nRequest:\n\nBody:\n\n{\n   "emailText":\n   "You won a lottery"\n}\n\nFlask receives data.\n\nBut Flask may not know:\n\nIs this JSON?\nXML?\nPlain text?\n\nSometimes Flask will reject the request.\n\nOr:\n\nrequest.get_json\(\)\n\nreturns:\n\nnull\n\nbecause Flask wasn't told the body is JSON.)/CreationDate(D:20260606220254+05'30)/F 28/M(D:20260606220254+05'30)/NM(79516b6a-7629-40fd-a4b3-437592fbf85b)/Name/Note/Popup 10642 0 R /Rect[ 170.581 629.981 188.277 650.817]/Subj()/Subtype/Text/T(Tanbir)/Type/Annot>>
endobj
